         <abstract>
            <p>We consider the boundary integral equation which arises when the Dirichlet problem in two dimensions is solved using a single-layer potential. A spectral Galerkin method is analyzed, suitable for the case of a smooth domain and smooth boundary data. The use of trigonometric polynomials rather than splines leads to fast convergence in Sobolev spaces of every order. As a result, there is rapid convergence of the approximate solution to the Dirichlet problem and all its derivatives uniformly up to the boundary.</p>
          </abstract>
